usage: git sclean [<options>]

Clean untracked and ignored files recursively

    -h|--help               display help
    -f|--force              clean even if work dir is dirty
    -d|--dsm-only           delete dangling submodules only
    <git-for options>       options for 'git for' when --recursive is specified
    
example:
    git sclean             # delete ignored files (stop if repo dirty)
    git sclean -f          # delete ignored files and dangling submodules
    git sclean -d          # clean dangling submodules only
